protection against severe disease, given infection
97.5% of people with some level of immunity are protected against severe disease
unvaccinated individuals whose immunity was conferred by natural infection have 47.5% less protection against severe disease than those whose strong or weak immunity was conferred by vaccination
90% of people with a prior Delta infection are protected against severe disease
70% of people who have completed a vaccine series are protected against severe Omicron
90% of people who have been boosted are protected against severe Omicron
the extent to which immunity is reduced, given infection with a prior variant
37.5% of weakly immune individuals can get reinfected with Delta
given prior infection with a pre-Omicron variant, 10% of strongly immune individuals can get reinfected with BA.1, BA.2, or BA.2.12.1
given prior infection with a pre-Omicron variant, 75% of weakly immune individuals can get reinfected with BA.1, BA.2, or BA.2.12.1
given prior infection with BA.1 or BA.2, 3% of strongly immune individuals can get reinfected with BA.2.12.1
given prior infection with BA.1 or BA.2, 25% of weakly immune individuals can get reinfected with BA.2.12.1
given prior infection with a pre-Omicron variant, 15% of strongly immune individuals can get reinfected with BA.4/5
given prior infection with a pre-Omicron variant, 80% of weakly immune individuals can get reinfected with BA.4/5
given prior infection with an Omicron variant, 4% of strongly immune individuals can get reinfected with BA.4/5
given prior infection with an Omicron variant, 40% of weakly immune individuals can get reinfected with BA.4/5
it takes 360 days for strong immunity to decay to weak immunity (weak immunity is assumed not to decay to no immunity)
immunity takes 1.25x longer to decay for those who have been boosted
2.2 wildtype seeds are planted each day in CO starting January 24th, 2020
1 Alpha seed is planted each day starting November 9th, 2020 and ending December 4th, 2020
1 Delta seed is planted each day starting March 7th, 2021 and ending April 11th, 2021
1 BA.1 seed is planted each day starting November 9th, 2021 and ending December 11th, 2021
5 BA.2 seeds are planted each day starting December 23rd, 2021 and ending February 2nd, 2022
5 BA.2.12.1 seeds are planted each day starting February 27th, 2022 and ending April 8th, 2022
5 BA.4/5 seeds are planted each day started April 5th, 2022 and ending May 15, 2022
Alpha is 1.5x more infectious than wildtype
Delta is 2.25x more infectious than wildtype
BA.1 is 2.25x more infectious than Delta (and 5.063x more infectious than wildtype)
BA.2 is 1.5x more infectious than Omicron (and 7.594x more infectious than wildtype)
BA.2.12.1 is 1.13x more infectious than BA.2 (and 8.581x more infectious than wildtype)
BA.4/5 is 1.13x more infectious than BA.2 (and 8.581x more infectious than wildtype)
wildtype has an incubation period of 2.5 days
Omicrons have 40% shorter incubation periods than wildtype
Omicrons have 67% higher recovery rates (i.e. shorter infectious periods) than wildtype
Omicrons have a 16.4% lower proportion of symptomatic infections for those with no or weak immunity compared to Delta
Omicrons have a 40.6% lower proportion of symptomatic infections for those who are vaccinated compared to Delta
Alpha sends 40% more people to the hospital compared to wildtype
Delta sends 2.38x more people to the hospital compared to wildtype
Omicrons send 16.7% fewer people to the hospital compared to wildtype
Omicrons have a 40% shorter length of stay than wildtype
Alpha has a 15% higher death rate than wildtype for those who are hospitalized
Delta has a 32% higher death rate than wildtype for those who are hospitalized
Omicron has the same death rate as Delta for those who are hospitalized (LIKELY WRONG)
Alpha has a 60% higher death rate than wildtype for those who are not hospitalized
Delta has a 3.28x higher death rate than wildtype for those who are not hospitalized
Omicron has an 86.775% lower death rate than wildtype for those who are not hospitalized
